<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-07-27T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-07-27T16:00:00-05:00" n="1585" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1585">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.918/7–2749: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-07-27T17:00:00-04:00">July 27,
                                    1949—5 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>885. Re Shanghai’s 2920 July 27 rptd Nanking 1640. If you have not
                            already done so, pls make strong representations Gould–Miner case
                            earliest.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>